<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1058,211,292]" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">
D i a g n o s i s: Among the 2 heretofore known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[808,885,212,233]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Agnatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="972" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[808,885,212,233]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">Agnatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[902,999,212,233]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">A. vaurei</emphasis>
most closely approximate 
<emphasis box="[371,470,241,262]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">A. dugesi</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode box="[488,582,241,262]" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">GORHAM</collectionCode>
), from which 
<emphasis box="[741,756,241,262]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[773,838,241,262]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">vaurei</emphasis>
specimens differ by showing a testaceous pronotal color. The pronotum is black in specimens of 
<emphasis box="[927,1029,270,291]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">A. dugesi.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1059,307,623]" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 7.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[673,753,307,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="973" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[895,980,307,329]" captionStart="Figs 278-281" captionStartId="97.[151,191,1524,1546]" captionTargetBox="[151,1059,197,1507]" captionTargetId="figure@97.[151,1059,197,1508]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="Figs 278-281: Habitus; (278) Phonius versus; (279) Agnatis curvabilis; (280) A. vaurieae; (281) Parapelonides aodontus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746800" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746800/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">Fig. 280</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium and antenna black; pterothorax, legs, and abdomen piceous; elytra mostly black with a bluish luster, epipleural fold testaceous. Head: Cranium coarsely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation box="[247,325,395,417]" captionStart="Figs 92-100" captionStartId="74.[151,191,872,894]" captionTargetBox="[175,1038,229,838]" captionTargetId="figure@74.[155,1062,203,862]" captionTargetPageId="74" captionText="Figs 92-100: Antennae; (92) Pyticeroides desodes; (93) Ichnea cerinis; (94) Agnatis vaurieae; (95) Ampleris amazon; (96) Nepsudia guenda; (97) Isoparis cassidilis; (98) Pelonium atrigonatium; (99) Aphelocerus yaguare; (100) Madoniella selvanegra." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746754/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres gradually wider from pedicel to 8 
<superScript attach="right" box="[1046,1059,391,405]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">th</superScript>
antennomere, capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 long triangular, antennomere 11 subrectangulate; eyes small, ommatidia small, ocular notch large, eye much narrower than frons (EW/FW 20/38). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[562,656,483,505]" captionStart="Figs 153-162" captionStartId="78.[151,191,1442,1464]" captionTargetBox="[174,1045,215,1409]" captionTargetId="figure@78.[153,1061,200,1429]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Figs 153-162: Pronota; (153) Agnatis vaurieae; (154) Pelonium atrigonatium; (155) Pujoliclerus variolus; (156) Epiphloeus prolixicornus; (157) Sirpa latiflava; (158) Neorthopleura turnbowi; (159) Aphelocerus yaguare; (160) A. copanus; (161) Amboakis mitaraka; (162) Ellipotoma makrosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746762/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
) transverse (PW/PL 93/80), anterior transverse depression absent; disc coarsely punctate, lateral tubercle absent, disc concave paralaterally; elytral asetiferous punctures absent, setiferous punctures small and profusely distributed throughout elytral disc (EL/EW 300/90); Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[414,502,600,623]" captionStart="Figs 213-218" captionStartId="85.[151,191,1262,1284]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetId="figure@85.[153,1061,202,1251]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="Figs 213-218: Aedeagi; (213) Perilypus virgulatus; (214) Agnatis curvabilis; (215) A. vaurieae; (216) Parapelonides naranjo; (217) Pyticara frontegalba; (218) Amboakis bermejo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746776" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746776/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">Fig. 215</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1059,638,689]" pageId="14" pageNumber="973">
Variation: Length 4.0-7.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[551,675,638,660]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="973" unit="mm" value="2.1" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.7">1.7-2.5 mm</quantity>
. Other than body size, the available specimens were quite homogeneous.
</paragraph>
